  "instructions": [
    "Preheat smoker to 225°F (110°C).",
    "Season beef brisket with salt, cumin, and chili powder.",
    "Place beef in smoker and cook for 4-5 hours, or until tender.",
    "While beef is cooking, combine chipotle peppers, onion, garlic, and lime juice in a blender.",
    "Blend until smooth and set aside.",
    "Once beef is done, remove from heat and let rest for 10 minutes.",
    "Shred beef with two forks and add chipotle mixture. Stir to combine.",
    "Warm tortillas by wrapping them in a damp paper towel and microwaving for 20-30 seconds.",
    "Assemble tacos with shredded beef, cilantro, and any desired toppings.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
